the bug being tested: the git ancestry query returning wrong results when hashes differ post-squash. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) Real git subprocess (or equivalent local bare repo with real git operations) is required to produce a valid squash-merged commit graph. (b) No LLM. (c) No multi-step agentic chain. REJECTION-GATE: Integration was considered; the disqualifying evidence is that the failure is caused by real git commit-graph topology after squash/rebase — no in-process module handoff produces this topology without real git operations.","test_description":"Create a local git repo. Commit two changes to a feature branch. Squash-merge the feature branch into main (producing a new commit hash that contains the same diff but with a different SHA). Delete or leave the feature branch tip with its original hashes. Run staleness detection and assert the feature branch is NOT classified as `stale-no-pr` (because the content is in main). Repeat the test using a rebase scenario. Assert that detection does not rely solely on commit-hash matching and correctly identifies that the branch content is present in main via diff-fingerprint, patch-id, or title matching as appropriate.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.77,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.03}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10047,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10047},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"912051f3-5423-45ac-b15a-9f988624ec0a","uuid":"cbe0d310-54af-41a6-a055-542cc194d42b"}
